cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method to sanitize the privacy of input feature maps in CNNs, which is related to privacy and security.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper deals with CNNs, which are a type of machine learning model.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely category as CNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as CNNs are a type of AI model and the paper proposes a method to improve their privacy.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper introduces a sample-and-hold based approximation scheme to sanitize the input feature maps, which involves algorithms and data structures.
